name: FInterpCurveVector2D
doc:
Describes an entire curve that is used to compute a 2D vector output value from a float input.
@note This is a mirror of TInterpCurve<FVector2D>, defined in InterpCurve.h

Points: Holds the collection of interpolation points.
bIsLooped: Specify whether the curve is looped or not
LoopKeyOffset: Specify the offset from the last point's input key corresponding to the loop point
